{"body": "It depends if you consider 'changed' to be 'equivalent to the beginning' or 'modified at some point.' If I start at nil, change to something, then change back to nil, you can look at it as \"start == end, no change\" or \"it changed to nil in the middle, and therefore, has changed.\"\r\n\r\nGiven the context of an ORM, the first definition makes more sense, which is what this PR does. So :+1:.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/10920603", "created_at": "2012-12-01T18:58:20Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/8391#issuecomment-10920603", "updated_at": "2012-12-01T18:58:20Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 8391, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/steveklabnik", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/233c279c012ebac792aaa805f966cbc7?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F0c22d45f31acf0f4192c8c12b7a55dee.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/received_events", "gravatar_id": "233c279c012ebac792aaa805f966cbc7", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "steveklabnik", "type": "User", "id": 27786, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523d92d4bd354364b9007f1d"}, "id": 10920603, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/8391"}
